# ============================================================================
# FINAL SECURITY NOTES
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. If you accidentally commit .env:
#    - Run: git rm --cached .env
#    - Run: git commit -m 'Remove .env'
#    - ROTATE all credentials immediately
#
# 2. To verify nothing sensitive is committing:
#    - Run: git status
#    - Look for any .env, *.key, secrets files
#    - If you see any, add them to .gitignore and rotate credentials
#
# 3. For already-committed secrets:
#    - Use: git filter-branch (complex)
#    - Recommended: Use GitHub's secret scanning feature
#    - Rotate all exposed credentials immediately
#
# ============================================================================
